WEBVTT

00:02.417 --> 00:03.375
DANI:

00:02.417 --> 00:03.375
Fried chicken,

00:03.417 --> 00:05.375
salad,

00:03.417 --> 00:05.375
lemonade...

00:05.417 --> 00:08.959
and our very own

00:05.417 --> 00:08.959
private shady spot.

00:09.000 --> 00:10.542
Thanks, Cody!

00:10.583 --> 00:12.125
No problem,

00:10.583 --> 00:12.125
sis!

00:12.166 --> 00:15.083
BLADES ( whispers ):

00:12.166 --> 00:15.083
I don't get it.

00:12.166 --> 00:15.083
If Dani likes Taylor,

00:15.125 --> 00:17.458
why does she make him

00:15.125 --> 00:17.458
eat her potato salad?

00:17.500 --> 00:19.208
I think that's her meatloaf.

00:19.250 --> 00:20.625
( buzzing )

00:24.041 --> 00:25.250
What was that?

00:25.291 --> 00:27.542
Oh, sorry, Taylor...

00:25.291 --> 00:27.542
picnic's over.

00:27.583 --> 00:29.083
Robot,

00:27.583 --> 00:29.083
Copter mode!

00:30.750 --> 00:32.250
(  action theme playing  )

00:35.208 --> 00:36.500
I'll call the team.

00:39.000 --> 00:41.375
HEATWAVE:

00:39.000 --> 00:41.375
Rescue Bots,

00:39.000 --> 00:41.375
roll to the rescue!

00:41.417 --> 00:42.750
( sirens blaring )

00:44.250 --> 00:45.834
( whistling )

00:48.291 --> 00:49.709
Not so close!

00:49.750 --> 00:51.917
Do you see what that thing

00:49.750 --> 00:51.917
does to metal?

00:51.959 --> 00:54.000
Dad,

00:51.959 --> 00:54.000
it's headed toward the docks!

00:54.041 --> 00:55.291
( buzzing )

00:58.750 --> 01:00.667
Boulder, follow me.

00:58.750 --> 01:00.667
We'll cut it off.

01:06.959 --> 01:08.375
( helicopter blades churning )

01:15.166 --> 01:16.959
( both gasp )

01:19.417 --> 01:21.834
♪  Routine patrol

01:19.417 --> 01:21.834
With four bots in stasis  ♪

01:21.875 --> 01:24.542
♪  Years later awoke

01:21.875 --> 01:24.542
In the strangest of places  ♪

01:24.583 --> 01:27.125
♪  Earth was their home now

01:24.583 --> 01:27.125
And in addition  ♪

01:27.166 --> 01:29.750
♪  Optimus Prime gave them

01:27.166 --> 01:29.750
This mission  ♪

01:29.792 --> 01:32.458
♪  Learn from the humans

01:29.792 --> 01:32.458
Serve and protect  ♪

01:32.500 --> 01:34.667
♪  Live in their world

01:32.500 --> 01:34.667
Earn their respect  ♪

01:34.709 --> 01:37.333
♪  A family of heroes

01:34.709 --> 01:37.333
Will be your allies  ♪

01:37.375 --> 01:40.125
♪  To others remain

01:37.375 --> 01:40.125
Robots in disguise  ♪

01:40.166 --> 01:42.792
♪  Rescue Bots

01:40.166 --> 01:42.792
Roll to the rescue  ♪

01:42.834 --> 01:45.083
♪  Humans in need

01:42.834 --> 01:45.083
Heroes indeed  ♪

01:45.125 --> 01:48.125
♪  Rescue Bots

01:45.125 --> 01:48.125
Roll to the rescue  ♪

01:48.166 --> 01:49.917
♪  Rescue Bots  ♪

01:59.291 --> 02:01.250
Back off and I'll smash it!

02:01.291 --> 02:02.667
MAN:

02:01.291 --> 02:02.667
Stop!

02:04.583 --> 02:05.959
( beeps )

02:06.000 --> 02:07.500
( buzzing slows and stops )

02:08.959 --> 02:11.709
That device is irreplaceable.

02:11.750 --> 02:13.208
Uncle Woodrow?

02:13.250 --> 02:15.208
( sighs )

02:13.250 --> 02:15.208
Woodrow.

02:16.542 --> 02:17.625
Uncle Woodrow!

02:17.667 --> 02:18.959
Why didn't you tell us

02:17.667 --> 02:18.959
you were coming?

02:19.000 --> 02:20.250
I can't believe it's you!

02:20.291 --> 02:21.542
Uncle?

02:21.583 --> 02:23.291
Human term for sibling

02:21.583 --> 02:23.291
of a parent.

02:23.333 --> 02:25.500
In this case--

02:23.333 --> 02:25.500
Chief's brother.

02:25.542 --> 02:27.333
Chief didn't tell us he was

02:25.542 --> 02:27.333
coming to visit.

02:27.375 --> 02:28.917
Or that he existed.

02:28.959 --> 02:30.291
Wonderful.

02:31.542 --> 02:32.792
( laughing )

02:32.834 --> 02:34.959
I'll answer your questions,

02:35.000 --> 02:37.333
just let me look at you

02:35.000 --> 02:37.333
a second.

02:37.375 --> 02:39.458
Cody,

02:37.375 --> 02:39.458
you've grown a foot.

02:39.500 --> 02:41.041
Now you'll need three socks.

02:41.083 --> 02:42.500
( laughs )

02:42.542 --> 02:45.500
Did you kids get

02:42.542 --> 02:45.500
my postcards from Dwarma?

02:45.542 --> 02:48.500
Or the scorpions I sent

02:45.542 --> 02:48.500
from Ecuador?

02:48.542 --> 02:50.500
Um...

02:48.542 --> 02:50.500
never got those.

02:50.542 --> 02:51.834
Oh.

02:51.875 --> 02:53.542
I thought I sent 'em...

02:53.583 --> 02:55.000
may have forgotten.

02:55.041 --> 02:56.875
Gee,

02:55.041 --> 02:56.875
imagine that.

02:56.917 --> 02:58.208
Woodrow,

02:56.917 --> 02:58.208
this, uh,

02:58.250 --> 03:00.041
floating menace belongs to you?

03:02.208 --> 03:04.667
Good to see you too,

03:02.208 --> 03:04.667
big brother.

03:04.709 --> 03:07.750
Come here,

03:04.709 --> 03:07.750
give me a decent hello.

03:07.792 --> 03:09.709
( grunting and groaning )

03:09.750 --> 03:11.250
Okay, Woody,

03:09.750 --> 03:11.250
okay...

03:11.291 --> 03:13.917
High-grade titanium...

03:13.959 --> 03:17.667
laser drill... self-propulsion

03:13.959 --> 03:17.667
and sonar tracking...

03:17.709 --> 03:19.250
That's quite a device,

03:17.709 --> 03:19.250
Uncle Woodrow.

03:19.291 --> 03:22.500
Yeah.

03:19.291 --> 03:22.500
It's my Deep Earth Scout.

03:22.542 --> 03:25.667
Designed to drill underground

03:22.542 --> 03:25.667
and collect data.

03:25.709 --> 03:28.625
And you won't believe

03:25.709 --> 03:28.625
what it found.

03:28.667 --> 03:30.083
This is it,

03:28.667 --> 03:30.083
Charlie.

03:30.125 --> 03:31.875
What I've been looking for

03:30.125 --> 03:31.875
my whole life.

03:31.917 --> 03:36.333
Evidence that aliens may have

03:31.917 --> 03:36.333
visited the earth centuries ago.

03:38.750 --> 03:41.709
Well, don't everybody get

03:38.750 --> 03:41.709
all excited at once.

03:41.750 --> 03:43.333
We're happy for you,

03:41.750 --> 03:43.333
Uncle Woodrow.

03:43.375 --> 03:44.959
It's-it's only that--

03:45.000 --> 03:47.375
I just wish your homecoming

03:45.000 --> 03:47.375
had been a little less...

03:47.417 --> 03:48.458
destructive.

03:48.500 --> 03:51.625
Hm...

03:48.500 --> 03:51.625
Sorry, Charlie.

03:51.667 --> 03:53.709
The DES must have

03:51.667 --> 03:53.709
accidentally activated

03:53.750 --> 03:55.125
when I was getting off

03:53.750 --> 03:55.125
the ferry.

03:56.125 --> 03:57.417
( sighs )

03:57.458 --> 04:00.041
Speaking of machines...

04:00.083 --> 04:01.458
( chuckles )

04:01.500 --> 04:04.333
Looks like you still have

04:01.500 --> 04:04.333
the best toys.

04:04.375 --> 04:06.458
Where on Earth did you get

04:04.375 --> 04:06.458
these guys, Charlie?

04:06.500 --> 04:08.583
Uh, they're our

04:06.500 --> 04:08.583
rescue robots.

04:08.625 --> 04:10.750
Uh, state-of-the-art

04:08.625 --> 04:10.750
emergency stuff.

04:10.792 --> 04:13.000
Watch what they can do,

04:10.792 --> 04:13.000
Uncle Woodrow!

04:13.041 --> 04:14.875
Robots,

04:13.041 --> 04:14.875
vehicle mode.

04:18.166 --> 04:20.208
Whoa.

04:20.250 --> 04:21.917
Impressive.

04:23.250 --> 04:24.625
Hey,

04:23.250 --> 04:24.625
what's the mileage like?

04:24.667 --> 04:26.208
( laughs )

04:28.083 --> 04:29.291
Now Woodrow,

04:28.083 --> 04:29.291
you c--

04:29.333 --> 04:30.625
Hey, what's for dinner?

04:30.667 --> 04:32.041
( groans )

04:32.083 --> 04:33.417
All right,

04:32.083 --> 04:33.417
go easy, Woodrow.

04:33.458 --> 04:35.875
This is not Dad's old jalopy.

04:36.291 --> 04:37.583
( siren blares )

04:37.625 --> 04:39.792
( engine roars )

04:45.083 --> 04:47.709
Well...

04:45.083 --> 04:47.709
that's Uncle Woodrow.

04:47.750 --> 04:49.208
Uncle Woodrow is an

04:47.750 --> 04:49.208
archeologist.

04:49.250 --> 04:51.166
Sort of.

04:49.250 --> 04:51.166
And an inventor.

04:51.208 --> 04:52.792
Sometimes.

04:52.834 --> 04:55.083
He's been around the world

04:52.834 --> 04:55.083
a lot...I think.

04:55.125 --> 04:57.458
He doesn't seem

04:55.125 --> 04:57.458
anything like the Chief.

04:57.500 --> 04:59.083
Look at me and Graham.

04:59.125 --> 05:00.709
Would you ever think

04:59.125 --> 05:00.709
a guy like me

05:00.750 --> 05:01.959
could have a brother

05:00.750 --> 05:01.959
like him?

05:02.000 --> 05:03.291
Come here you.

05:02.000 --> 05:03.291
Wha--?

05:03.333 --> 05:04.959
Kade!

05:03.333 --> 05:04.959
Ha, ha!

05:06.667 --> 05:08.959
I'm sure he meant it

05:06.667 --> 05:08.959
in a nice way.

05:10.792 --> 05:13.208
All my research

05:10.792 --> 05:13.208
has convinced me.

05:13.250 --> 05:16.333
Pictographs, pyramids,

05:13.250 --> 05:16.333
Stonehenge...

05:16.375 --> 05:19.875
They're alien artifacts,

05:16.375 --> 05:19.875
every one of them.

05:19.917 --> 05:23.500
But, uh, you kids probably don't

05:19.917 --> 05:23.500
believe in aliens, do you?

05:23.542 --> 05:26.041
It could happen...

05:23.542 --> 05:26.041
I'd consider the evidence...

05:26.083 --> 05:28.291
Nope. No way.

05:26.083 --> 05:28.291
I wouldn't say that we don't...

05:28.333 --> 05:30.792
Sit down and eat,

05:28.333 --> 05:30.792
Charlie.

05:30.834 --> 05:32.959
Dinner doesn't

05:30.834 --> 05:32.959
serve itself

05:33.000 --> 05:35.166
somebody has to cook

05:33.000 --> 05:35.166
and clean up.

05:37.000 --> 05:39.959
Well, uh,

05:37.000 --> 05:39.959
That's good, old Charlie...

05:40.000 --> 05:41.959
Nose to the grindstone.

05:42.000 --> 05:44.083
Say, pass the potatoes,

05:42.000 --> 05:44.083
will you?

05:44.125 --> 05:47.750
Then I'll show you

05:44.125 --> 05:47.750
what my DES found...

05:49.125 --> 05:50.917
HEATWAVE:

05:49.125 --> 05:50.917
Ugh, I don't get it.

05:50.959 --> 05:54.417
Why is Chief's brother so eager

05:50.959 --> 05:54.417
to find an alien, anyway?

05:54.458 --> 05:56.208
I know.

05:56.250 --> 05:58.709
With all the amazing things

05:56.250 --> 05:58.709
humans have on their own planet,

05:58.750 --> 06:01.166
why bother searching

05:58.750 --> 06:01.166
for... us?

06:01.208 --> 06:03.125
Because we're awesome.

06:03.166 --> 06:05.875
But who sends scorpions

06:03.166 --> 06:05.875
as gifts?

06:05.917 --> 06:07.333
No thank you.

06:07.375 --> 06:08.959
Who knows?

06:09.000 --> 06:11.041
Maybe he brought some scorpions

06:09.000 --> 06:11.041
along with him...

06:11.083 --> 06:12.500
( yelps )

06:12.542 --> 06:13.917
Very funny.

06:13.959 --> 06:15.625
All I know is,

06:15.667 --> 06:18.000
Woodrow Burns forced me

06:15.667 --> 06:18.000
to drive over the speed limit.

06:18.041 --> 06:20.500
And I was

06:18.041 --> 06:20.500
helpless to stop him.

06:20.542 --> 06:23.542
WOODROW:

06:20.542 --> 06:23.542
Now most people look for aliens

06:20.542 --> 06:23.542
in outer space...

06:25.291 --> 06:27.792
But my research made me

06:25.291 --> 06:27.792
realize...

06:27.834 --> 06:30.500
we should be looking

06:27.834 --> 06:30.500
in inner space.

06:30.542 --> 06:32.875
Underneath the earth.

06:32.917 --> 06:37.208
So I built and dispatched six

06:32.917 --> 06:37.208
DES spheres to gather data

06:37.250 --> 06:39.333
from all across the planet.

06:39.375 --> 06:41.542
Five of the devices are still

06:39.375 --> 06:41.542
out there somewhere,

06:41.583 --> 06:43.500
gathering data...

06:43.542 --> 06:47.458
But this baby uncovered all

06:43.542 --> 06:47.458
the evidence I need.

06:47.500 --> 06:51.750
Right in my old hometown.

06:47.500 --> 06:51.750
Well, under it.

06:51.792 --> 06:56.375
A cavern containing proof of

06:51.792 --> 06:56.375
a lost alien civilization.

06:56.417 --> 06:58.125
Housing structures...

06:58.166 --> 07:00.583
Looks like rock formations

06:58.166 --> 07:00.583
to me.

07:00.709 --> 07:02.291
Communication signals...

07:02.333 --> 07:03.291
( echoes )

07:03.333 --> 07:05.792
Or water dripping...

07:05.834 --> 07:08.417
Even aliens themselves...

07:10.333 --> 07:11.834
Shadows on the wall.

07:11.875 --> 07:14.917
That's the difference

07:11.875 --> 07:14.917
between us, Charlie.

07:14.959 --> 07:17.458
I'm curious to know for sure.

07:23.250 --> 07:26.834
So I'm going to borrow the

07:23.250 --> 07:26.834
town's old Forger, you remember?

07:26.875 --> 07:29.458
We found it when were kids,

07:26.875 --> 07:29.458
down where the tunnels end.

07:29.500 --> 07:32.750
That giant driller?

07:29.500 --> 07:32.750
It hasn't been used in years.

07:32.792 --> 07:35.000
I think

07:32.792 --> 07:35.000
I can get it running.

07:35.041 --> 07:37.959
Then I follow the coordinates

07:35.041 --> 07:37.959
the DES brought back...

07:38.000 --> 07:40.583
and I'll finally have my proof.

07:40.625 --> 07:42.250
That is awesome!

07:42.291 --> 07:44.667
Hey, you can come with me,

07:42.291 --> 07:44.667
Cody. All of you.

07:44.709 --> 07:48.000
A once-in-a-lifetime journey to

07:44.709 --> 07:48.000
the center of the Earth.

07:48.041 --> 07:49.834
Oh, wow...

07:48.041 --> 07:49.834
Sign me up!

07:49.875 --> 07:52.083
Sounds great!

07:49.875 --> 07:52.083
Woodrow...

07:52.125 --> 07:54.250
My family can't just drop

07:52.125 --> 07:54.250
everything and go off

07:54.291 --> 07:56.458
on some spur-of-the moment

07:54.291 --> 07:56.458
expedition.

07:56.500 --> 07:58.375
Especially--

07:58.417 --> 08:00.917
Especially with me,

07:58.417 --> 08:00.917
right?

08:00.959 --> 08:03.333
Give us a minute,

08:00.959 --> 08:03.333
will you, kids?

08:06.500 --> 08:09.583
You've always been the dreamer

08:06.500 --> 08:09.583
of the family, I get that.

08:09.625 --> 08:11.500
But you never

08:09.625 --> 08:11.500
see one dream through

08:11.542 --> 08:13.041
before you're off,

08:11.542 --> 08:13.041
chasing another.

08:13.083 --> 08:14.375
Charlie,

08:13.083 --> 08:14.375
that's not--

08:14.417 --> 08:15.917
Like when we were kids,

08:15.959 --> 08:17.625
I'd have to put out

08:15.959 --> 08:17.625
the fires you started

08:17.667 --> 08:19.709
with your bottle rockets,

08:17.667 --> 08:19.709
and you'd already be off

08:19.750 --> 08:21.500
building a flying bicycle.

08:21.542 --> 08:24.000
Well not all of my expeditions

08:21.542 --> 08:24.000
have gone well,

08:24.041 --> 08:26.000
I'll give you that.

08:24.041 --> 08:26.000
But this time,

08:26.041 --> 08:28.000
with you and the kids along

08:26.041 --> 08:28.000
to keep me focused--

08:28.041 --> 08:29.959
We're not going,

08:28.041 --> 08:29.959
Woodrow.

08:30.000 --> 08:32.375
And you can't borrow

08:30.000 --> 08:32.375
the Tunnel Forger.

08:32.417 --> 08:33.750
That's the end of it.

08:35.375 --> 08:36.375
Sorry, kids.

08:36.417 --> 08:37.417
( button beeps )

08:37.458 --> 08:39.000
( buzzing )

08:41.709 --> 08:45.583
The human sibling relationship

08:41.709 --> 08:45.583
appears to be a complex one.

08:45.625 --> 08:47.792
Don't Bots

08:45.625 --> 08:47.792
have brothers or sisters?

08:47.834 --> 08:50.667
Nope.

08:47.834 --> 08:50.667
We're all on our own.

08:50.709 --> 08:52.375
Lucky.

08:52.417 --> 08:54.709
But it must

08:52.417 --> 08:54.709
get kind of lonely.

08:57.458 --> 09:00.750
HEATWAVE:

08:57.458 --> 09:00.750
There. I wasn't sure at first,

08:57.458 --> 09:00.750
but--

09:00.792 --> 09:02.917
OPTIMUS:

09:00.792 --> 09:02.917
You were right to contact me,

09:00.792 --> 09:02.917
Heatwave.

09:02.959 --> 09:04.625
So that blue crystal is...

09:04.667 --> 09:07.333
Energon. A new supply

09:04.667 --> 09:07.333
that could benefit

09:07.375 --> 09:09.917
all Autobots

09:07.375 --> 09:09.917
for years to come.

09:09.959 --> 09:13.083
Heatwave,

09:09.959 --> 09:13.083
prepare your team.

09:13.125 --> 09:15.625
I will be arriving in the

09:13.125 --> 09:15.625
morning...

09:15.667 --> 09:17.041
And then,

09:17.083 --> 09:18.875
we go underground.

09:22.709 --> 09:24.500
( grease sizzling )

09:26.500 --> 09:28.250
Dad, where's

09:26.500 --> 09:28.250
Uncle Woodrow?

09:28.291 --> 09:30.750
Must've gone out early.

09:28.291 --> 09:30.750
Who knows where.

09:32.750 --> 09:34.333
I might have an idea.

09:41.250 --> 09:42.667
Looks like you were right,

09:41.250 --> 09:42.667
Cody.

09:42.709 --> 09:44.000
Wait here, okay,

09:42.709 --> 09:44.000
Boulder?

09:44.041 --> 09:45.792
(  action theme plays  )

09:45.834 --> 09:47.166
Uncle Woodrow!

09:49.333 --> 09:51.291
Uncle Woodrow,

09:49.333 --> 09:51.291
what are you doing?

09:51.333 --> 09:53.625
Well, I recharged

09:51.333 --> 09:53.625
the power cells...

09:53.667 --> 09:57.125
Now I just have to enter the

09:53.667 --> 09:57.125
coordinates for the cavern,

09:57.166 --> 09:59.333
and the Forger can start

09:57.166 --> 09:59.333
digging.

09:59.375 --> 10:02.375
But my dad--

09:59.375 --> 10:02.375
Your dad thinks my expeditions

10:02.417 --> 10:05.166
are hare-brained. That I

10:02.417 --> 10:05.166
don't think things through.

10:05.208 --> 10:08.250
No offense, Uncle Woodrow,

10:05.208 --> 10:08.250
but I'm not sure

10:08.291 --> 10:10.917
that stealing the Forger is the

10:08.291 --> 10:10.917
best way to prove him wrong.

10:10.959 --> 10:12.250
( laughs )

10:12.291 --> 10:14.208
You're probably right,

10:12.291 --> 10:14.208
Cody.

10:14.250 --> 10:16.041
But you have

10:14.250 --> 10:16.041
big brothers.

10:16.083 --> 10:20.208
You know how a nod from them is

10:16.083 --> 10:20.208
the nicest feeling in the world.

10:20.250 --> 10:22.417
I just want to show

10:20.250 --> 10:22.417
your dad that...

10:22.458 --> 10:24.875
I'm capable of doing something

10:22.458 --> 10:24.875
he can be proud of.

10:25.959 --> 10:27.250
( beeping )

10:27.291 --> 10:28.625
( engine powers up )

10:28.667 --> 10:29.625
( electricity flares )

10:29.667 --> 10:30.959
What's happening?

10:33.959 --> 10:36.166
The cells must have surged.

10:36.208 --> 10:37.542
We're on auto-pilot!

10:41.375 --> 10:42.667
What?

10:42.709 --> 10:44.000
CODY:

10:42.709 --> 10:44.000
Robot,

10:42.709 --> 10:44.000
get us out!

10:46.709 --> 10:48.417
( grunts )

10:51.709 --> 10:53.166
